{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/2711", "repo": "rails", "body": "@tenderlove: I can see that the implementation of `delegate` uses `__send__` in the `module_eval` string - why is this necessary? Do we want people to delegate to private methods? And wouldn't it be faster to simply do:\r\n\r\n```ruby\r\nmodule_eval(<<-EOS, file, line - 1)\r\n  def #{method_prefix}#{method}(*args, &block)\r\n    #{to}.#{method}(*args, &block)\r\n  end\r\nEOS\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis doesn't solve the problem with `*args`, but at least the stack depth would be the same, and we wouldn't need to call `__send__`.", "_id": {"$oid": "523840ecbd3543c151010950"}, "issue_id": 2711, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/1921031", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/2711#issuecomment-1921031", "updated_at": "2011-08-27T19:20:49Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dasch/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dasch/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dasch/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dasch/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/dasch", "login": "dasch", "gravatar_id": "a9cc05e6a7866e5fa9a7d107b5070174", "html_url": "https://github.com/dasch", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dasch/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dasch/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dasch/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/a9cc05e6a7866e5fa9a7d107b5070174?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fc6862d63b17d713ee14f3a405d9fde77.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dasch/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 6351, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dasch/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2011-08-27T19:20:49Z", "id": 1921031, "owner": "rails"}
